	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				* NPCs are now bound by the same Line of Sight rules as player characters. (An NPC must be able to &quot;see&quot; you to hit you with a spell.)<BR>
<BR>
* NPCs are now bound by spell casting distance rules. Meaning, an NPC's spell will no longer connect from halfway across the zone. (We want spellcasters to be challenging -- Not a deathtrap that a person has no ability to run away from.)<BR>
<BR>
What's with these 2 statements. I have noticed that the froglok wizzies in LGuk still cast from around corners. Saw an undead froglok wizard last night in the alcove on the other side of the river that goes to the bedroom area. As soon as I saw it start casting, I high tailed it back towards the zone. I had already rounded the first corner, had run up the lower ramp to where the 2 live frogloks are stationed, and was rounding the corner between them, when I was struck for 200+ points. So I know I was way out of line of sight and should have been out of it's range. Then as I ran up the ramp by the one live froggy, turned right and ran the short distance to the zone, I stopped and turned around so that my right shoulder was at the zone(I would be able to take a small right step to zone if needed). Anyway, I was immediately struck for another 200+ points and the wizard was still not in sight. I couldn't even see the live one that stands guard at the corner.<BR>
<BR>
Guess what I'm saying is that if I can't land a song because I can't see it, than the mobs should not be able to land a spell either. 
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
